{
  "genre": "lofi",
  "mode": "energize",
  "mixStrategy": "FREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (Electric Bass, GM 33) owns 20-300Hz with MIDI 30-45, providing the rhythmic and harmonic foundation locked to kick drum patterns. Chords (Warm Pad, GM 89) fill 300Hz-2kHz with sustained 7th voicings in MIDI 50-67, creating the warm harmonic bed. Melody (Electric Piano/Rhodes, GM 4) sits in 1-8kHz with MIDI 62-79, playing jazzy melodic phrases that weave between chord tones and scale passing tones. Drums (GM 0 ch10) span full spectrum rhythmically \u2014 kick (36) locks with bass on beats 1 and the 'and' of 2, snare on 2 and 4 for boom-bap feel, closed hi-hats (42) on 8th notes with ghost note velocity variation. RHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Bass and kick always land together. Snare provides backbeat. Rhodes melody phrases breathe in gaps between snare hits, with syncopated anticipations. Hi-hats provide continuous 8th-note pulse. HARMONIC UNITY: All tracks follow the same 8-bar chord loop (2 bars each): Em7 (ii7) \u2192 A7 (V7) \u2192 Dmaj7 (Imaj7) \u2192 Dmaj7, then Dmaj7 \u2192 Bm7 (vi7) \u2192 Em7 (ii7) \u2192 A7 (V7). Each chord lasts ~4.17s (2 bars at 115 BPM). ENERGY ARC over 6 segments (~7.5s each): 0.4 (sparse intro, soft velocity) \u2192 0.6 (drums enter fuller) \u2192 0.8 (melody gets more active, bass walks) \u2192 0.9 (full groove, dense hi-hats) \u2192 1.0 (peak energy, all tracks dense and punchy) \u2192 0.7 (pull back for outro cooldown). This creates a driving, rhythmic lo-fi hip hop track that builds energy through density and velocity increases while maintaining the relaxed jazzy warmth of the genre.",
